repository-artifact: "https://huggingface.co/athena129/Gemma4Defense-2B"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - cybersecurity
  - cti
  - cwe-classification
  - fine-tuning
  - lora
  - gemma
abstract: >
  Gemma4Defense-2B is a 2.3B-parameter language model fine-tuned from
  Gemma-4-E2B-it for CWE classification and cyber threat intelligence
  multiple-choice tasks. Under Cisco's Foundation-Sec evaluation protocol
  (arXiv:2504.21039), it retains 98.6% of Foundation-Sec-Instruct-8B's
  CTI-RCM accuracy at one-quarter the parameter count, while exceeding its
  CTI-MCQ by +10.5 points (5-trial mean). Companion model CyberSecQwen-4B
  trained with the same recipe on Qwen3-4B-Instruct-2507 converges to
  within 0.9 points on CTI-RCM, demonstrating recipe portability across
  model families.
